A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing every third Thursday in April as Biomedical Research Day; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, biomedical research plays a crucial role in advancing medical knowledge and
4 improving healthcare outcomes for both humans and animals, and biomedical research is the
5 broad area of science that looks for ways to prevent and treat diseases that cause illness and
6 death in people and in animals; and
7 WHEREAS, animal studies are indispensable for the development of new treatments and
8 cures that benefit human and animal health alike; and
9 WHEREAS, Biomedical Research Day serves as an opportunity to increase public awareness
10 about the vital contributions of animals to biomedical research and the resulting medical
11 advancements; and
12 WHEREAS, it is essential to recognize the dedication and hard work of professionals such
13 as biomedical technicians, animal care technicians, biomedical veterinarians, veterinary
14 technicians, and cage wash technicians, who contribute tirelessly to the field of biomedical
15 research; and
