16 WHEREAS, Biomedical Research Day also aims to highlight career opportunities in
17 biomedical research and laboratory animal care, fostering a research advocacy community
18 committed to compassionate animal care and the pursuit of scientific knowledge.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
20 the members of this body:
21 (1) Recognize every third Thursday in April as Biomedical Research Day;
22 (2) Acknowledge the importance of animal studies in the development of new treatments
23 and cures for both human and animal diseases, and we pledge our support for the
24 compassionate care of animals needed for research purposes;
25 (3) Commend the dedication and hard work of biomedical technicians, animal care
26 technicians, biomedical veterinarians, veterinary technicians, and cage wash technicians,
27 whose efforts contribute significantly to the advancement of biomedical research;
28 (4) Encourage educational initiatives that promote understanding of the vital role animals
29 play in biomedical research and highlight career opportunities in this field, thereby
30 fostering a community of advocates for scientific progress and animal welfare; and
31 (5) Call upon individuals, organizations, and policymakers to join this body in recognizing
32 and supporting Biomedical Research Day and its objectives of promoting awareness,
33 honoring contributions, and advocating for compassionate animal care in biomedical
34 research.
35 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
36 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
37 public and the press.
